    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> basa fillet[s]</strong> to a plate and drizzle your <strong>soy sauce</strong> all over, turn the fish several times until all the soy sauce has been absorbed</p><p>Sprinkle your <strong>cornflour </strong>all over and rub it into both sides of the fish until fully coated, then set aside for later \u2013 this is your <strong>coated basa</strong></p><p>Tip: Coat the fish in the cornflour one side at a time to avoid stickiness!</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-crispy-basa-with-tamarind-sauce/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice your<strong> shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Chop half your <strong>red chilli[es] </strong>into rounds, then chop the<strong> remaining chilli</strong> finely</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-crispy-basa-with-tamarind-sauce/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> white long grain rice</strong> and 400ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[600ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[800ml] </span><strong>cold water </strong>to a pot with a lid and bring to a boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for an initial 12 min</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-crispy-basa-with-tamarind-sauce/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil half a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> (enough to cover the base of the pan) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> coated basa </strong>and cook for 8-9 min, turning once halfway until golden, crisp and cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>Thai-style crispy basa</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-crispy-basa-with-tamarind-sauce/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the fish is cooking, combine your <strong>tamarind paste</strong>,<strong> fish sauce</strong>, 2 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [260ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> \u2013 this is your<strong> tamarind stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-crispy-basa-with-tamarind-sauce/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the rice has had an initial 12 min, trim, then add your <strong>green beans</strong> to the pot</p><p>Cook, covered, for a further 5-8 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice and <strong>green beans</strong> are cooked</p><p>Once done, remove the pot from the heat and keep covered until serving</p><p>Heat a separate pot with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium heat</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-crispy-basa-with-tamarind-sauce/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add the<strong> sliced shallot</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and<strong> chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add the<strong> tamarind stock</strong>, bring to the boil and cook for 4-5 min or until thickened slightly \u2013 this is your <strong>tamarind sauce</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander </strong>roughly, including the stalks</p><p>Trim, then slice your<strong> spring onion[s]</strong> finely</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-crispy-basa-with-tamarind-sauce/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> Thai-style crispy basa</strong> with the <strong>cooked rice</strong> <strong>& green beans</strong> to the side</p><p>Tip: For fancy presentation, press the rice into a small bowl and turn out</p><p>Drizzle the fish with the <strong>tamarind sauce </strong>and top it with the <strong>chopped coriander</strong>, <strong>sliced spring onion</strong> and<strong> chilli rounds</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
